	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I always wanted to learn some basic electronic in the past but never had the chance to find the time to do it.  I would like to read on the subject and I know I could "just f$%#!@ google it" but I don't know which one is good since it's not my field.  I'm a little bit concerned to end up on the "gba guy" of electronics.. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" />
<br />
<br />Is there any tutorial people recommend on the subject? I should be able to have access to some part easily like a breadboard, resistances etc.
<br />
<br />My goal is not to make something complicated like a powerpak but more like learning the basic and having fun with simple circuits. Any information on the subject will be greatly appreciated.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


