	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You could somehow ( <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /> ) get a copy of Electronics for Dummies, which I found very helpful. It explains a lot of fundamentals of Electronics that I didn't understand, and it helped me to understand them a lot better. It also says what you should have a constant supply of if you want to be working with electronics often among other things. I didn't finish the whole thing, and I didn't wrap my mind around everything they said because I kind of skimmed through the first part, but it seems to be a very good book, and I'd highly recommend it.
<br />
<br />Other than that, if anyone has good tutorials, I too would be very interested because I think electronics are quite fascinating. I can't believe someone came up with the concepts behind them and more than that I can't believe they work.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


